OL,3,C100 years on: How one of the world's
OL,4,Coldest buildings was found in Jersey
OL,6,FField Archaeologist Dr Herve Duval-
OL,7,FGatignol at the Societe Jersiaise
OL,8,Fsays: "There are a couple of mysteries
OL,9,Fabout the place, especially around how
OL,10,Fit was used.
OL,12,F"The middle part, the sanctuary, was
OL,13,Fdefinitely much more than just a
OL,14,Fburial place, it was probably a
OL,15,Fceremonial place. Of course when we
OL,16,Fthink of La Hougue Bie, we are also
OL,17,Fthinking of its orientation to the
OL,18,Feast. During a particular time of
OL,19,Fyear, the light is able to reflect on
OL,20,Fthe stones during the Equinox."
