OL,3,C100 years on: How one of the world's
OL,4,Coldest buildings was found in Jersey
OL,6,FA massive rubble mound was built on
OL,7,Ftop, faced with dry stone walling.
OL,8,FThis was enlarged over time by adding
OL,9,Fbanks of earth and stone.
OL,11,FThe passage grave remained open for
OL,12,Fmany centuries before it was finally
OL,13,Fsealed shut.
OL,15,FThe tomb remained hidden and intact
OL,16,Funtil 1924 when it was finally
OL,17,Fdiscovered and unearthed by a young
OL,18,Fman called Arthur, who later became
OL,19,Fknown as Dr Mourant.
