OL,3,C100 years on: How one of the world's
OL,4,Coldest buildings was found in Jersey
OL,6,FA number of artefacts were recovered
OL,7,Ffrom the site during its first
OL,8,Fexcavation in 1925:
OL,10,FThe remains of 19 pottery vessels
OL,11,Fknown as vase-supports were excavated
OL,12,Ffrom the centre of the chamber. It
OL,13,Fappears that the items were
OL,14,Fdeliberately broken, perhaps as part
OL,15,Fof a ritual.
OL,17,FTwo intact pots were placed at the
OL,18,Fedge of the platform. They seem to
OL,19,Fhave had a special ritual purpose,
OL,20,Fsuch as altars or offertories.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/13
