OL,3,C100 years on: How one of the world's
OL,4,Coldest buildings was found in Jersey
OL,6,FThe practice of depositing limpet
OL,7,Fshells with interred bodies seems to
OL,8,Fbe a specific custom of the Channel
OL,9,FIslands which has helped preserved
OL,10,Fskeletal remains and it is conceivable
OL,11,Fthat this was intended.
OL,13,FA small quantity oyster shells were
OL,14,Falso found on the platform at the
OL,15,Fwestern end of the chamber.
OL,17,FCattle, sheep, pig and bird bones were
OL,18,Ffound scattered on the floor of the
OL,19,Fchamber.
